revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== Borrowed from {{bor|en|ja|山中|tr=Yamanaka}}. ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun|Yamanakas}} # {{surname|en|from=Japanese}}. ===Statistics=== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Yamanaka'' is the 30509<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 765 individuals. ''Yamanaka'' is most common among Asian/Pacific Islander (81.05%) individuals. ===Anagrams=== * {{anagrams|en|a=aaaakmny|Nakayama}} ---- ==Japanese== ===Romanization=== {{ja-romaji}} # {{ja-romanization of|やまなか}} ---- ==Portuguese== ===Etymology=== Borrowed from {{bor|pt|ja|中山|tr=Yamanaka}}. ===Proper noun=== {{pt-proper noun|m|g2=f}} # {{surname|pt|from=Japanese}}
